Binary search is like being the Sherlock Holmes of sorted arrays. You donâ€™t search every element. It is a divide-and-conquer algorithm used to find the position of a target value within a sorted array. If the element exists, it returns its index. If not, it returns -1 (aka the â€œNopeâ€ index).
